to make changes directly : 

touch or mkdir  file/dir
git add <files/dir>
git commit -m "message"
git push oring master


Using branches , here the workflow

# Start a new branch e
git checkout -b new-feature master
or 
git branch <name of the branch/feature>
git checkout <name of the branch>

# Edit some files
git add <file>
git commit -m "Start a feature"


# Merge in the new-feature branch
git branch new_branch
git checkout new_branch
edit the file 
git add file 
git commit -a -m "message"
git push 
git checkout master 
git merge new_branch 
git push 


##this is to create and automagically change to branch 
git branch -d new-feature
